==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Siphonal
<hw>Si"phon*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
a siphon; resembling a siphon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Siphonal stomach</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
stomach which is tubular and bent back upon itself, like a siphon, as in
the salmon.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Siphonarid</ent>⟦br⟧
